1 before January 1, 2024, the tax shall be four and one-half
2 percent (4.5%) of net income As used in this subsection:
3 1. "Balance in the BRTF at the end of a fiscal year" means the budget
4 reserve trust fund account established in KRS 48.705 and includes
5 the following amounts and actions resulting from the final close of
6 the fiscal year:
7 a. The amount of moneys in the fund at the end of a fiscal year;
8 b. All close-out actions related to a budget reduction plan under KRS
9 48.130 or as modified in a branch budget bill; and
10 c. All close-out actions related to the surplus expenditure plan under
11 KRS 48.140 or as modified in a branch budget bill;
12 2. "GF appropriations" means the authorization by the General
13 Assembly to expend GF moneys, excluding:
14 a. Continuing appropriations;
15 b. Any appropriation to the budget reserve trust fund;
16 c. Any lump-sum appropriation to a state-administered retirement
17 system, as defined in KRS 7A.210, that is in excess of the
18 appropriations specifically budgeted to meet the recurring
19 statutorily required contributions or recurring actuarially
20 determined contributions for a state-administered retirement
21 system under KRS 21.525, 61.565, 61.702, 78.635, 78.5536, or
22 161.550, as applicable; and
23 d. Any appropriation from the budget reserve trust fund account
24 established in KRS 48.705 that is:
25 i. Solely supported by moneys from the budget reserve trust fund
26 account; and
27 ii. Specifically identified in the appropriation language as not being a
