1 GF appropriation for the purposes of this section;
2 3. "GF moneys" means receipts deposited in the general fund defined
3 in KRS 48.010, excluding tobacco moneys deposited in the fund
4 established in KRS 248.654;
5 4. "IIT equivalent" means the amount of reduction in GF moneys
6 resulting from a one (1) percentage point reduction to the
7 individual income tax rate and shall be calculated by dividing the
8 actual individual income tax receipts for the fiscal year under
9 consideration by:
10 a. The sum of:
11 i. The individual income tax rate, expressed as a percentage, for the
12 first six (6) months of the fiscal year; and
13 ii. The individual income tax rate, expressed as a percentage, for the
14 second six (6) months of the fiscal year; and
15 b. Dividing the sum determined in subdivision a. of this
16 subparagraph by two (2); and
17 5. For analysis through fiscal year 2024-2025 and for reporting
18 through September 5, 2025:
19 a. "Reduction conditions" means:
20 i. The balance in the BRTF at the end of a fiscal year shall be equal
21 to or greater than ten percent (10%) of the GF moneys for that
22 fiscal year; and
23 ii. GF moneys at the end of a fiscal year shall be equal to or greater
24 than GF appropriations for that fiscal year plus the IIT equivalent
25 for that fiscal year; and
26 b. "Tax rate reduction" means the current tax rate minus five-tenths
27 of one percent (0.5%).
