2 (d) For taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2023, but prior
3 to January 1, 2024, the tax shall be four and one-half percent
4 (4.5%) of net income.
5 (e) For taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2024, but before
6 January 1, 2026, the tax shall be four percent (4%) of net income.
7 (f) For taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2026, the tax
8 shall be three and one-half percent (3.5%) of net income.
9 (g) 1. For taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2027, the
10 income tax rate may be reduced according to the annual process
11 established in:
12 a. Subparagraph 2. or 3. of this paragraph; and
13 b. Subparagraph 4. of this paragraph.
14 2. a. The Office of State Budget Director shall review the
15 reduction conditions for the fiscal year 2024-2025 no later than
16 September 1, 2025.
17 b. After reviewing the reduction conditions under subdivision a. of
18 this subparagraph, the Office of State Budget Director shall, no
19 later than September 5, 2025, report to the Interim Joint
20 Committee on Appropriations and Revenue:
21 i. Whether the reduction conditions for the fiscal year 2024-2025
22 have been met; and
23 ii. The amounts associated with each item within the reduction
24 conditions used for making that determination.
25 c. i. If the reduction conditions have been met for fiscal year
26 2024-2025, the General Assembly may take action to reduce the
27 rate in paragraph (f) of this subsection for the taxable year
